condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Article 5.01 | Description :The DESO Implementation Agreement has been executed on behalf of the Borrower andDESO. Before Effectiveness. | Due Date :31-Aug-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, A. 1. (a) | Description :The Borrower should maintain an Advisory Council with the powersand responsibilities set forth in the Operational Manual During the implementation of the Project | Due Date :31-Aug-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, A. 1. (b) | Description :The Borrower shall have UAPAS fully staffed with personnel withexperience and qualifications satisfactory to the Bank, with the powers and responsibilities set forth in the Operational Manual.Two months from the Effective Date | Due Date :25-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, B. 1. (b) | Description :The Borrower shall enter into an agreement with each of theCooperating Entities under terms and conditions satisfactory to the Bank. Prior to initiating activities for the benefit of aCooperation Entity | Due Date :31-Aug-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, E. 1. | Description :The Borrower shall furnish to the Bank for its approval, inaccordance with the Resettlement Policy Framework, any needed Resettlement Plan, and carry out such Resettlement Plans inaccordance with their terms. Prior to initiating the bidding process for any contract for construction works that call forresettlement | Due Date :25-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, E. 2. | Description :The Borrower shall carry out the Project in accordance with theEnvironmental Management Plan and furnish to the Bank any needed documentation as required by this Environmental Management Plan.During the implementation of the Project | Due Date :25-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, E. 3. | Description :The Borrower shall establish a panel to review the safety of theJacarecica I and II and the Poção da Ribeira dams, and furnish tothe Bank an action plan to address deficiencies, if any, andevidence of the actions taken to address any such deficiencies. Prior to initiating any activities under Component II of theProject, for the Jacarecica I and II and Poção da Ribeira dams. | Due Date :25-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, E. 4 | Description :The Borrower shall submit to the Bank the EA and the licenses priorto initiating the works for the Aracaju wastewater treatment plant | Due Date :30-Dec-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, E. 5 | Description :The Borrower shall ensure TOR for consultancy services satisfactoryto the Bank and incorporating safeguards provisions. Throughoutimplementation | Due Date :31-Aug-2012

title.narrative: Adoption of water and soil conservation practices by rural producers who benefit from irrigation kits
Demarcation, preservation, conservation and recovery of protected areas in water supply reservoirs in the Sergipe River Basin
Training of rural producers and rural technical assistance agents as replicators of technologies and practices of soil and water conservation targeting the enhancement of natural resources management
Number of people benefiting from improved water supply system by the Project
Water Users Benefited from Improved Irrigation System
Improved efficiency irrigation techniques implemented in agricultural areas targeted by the Project
People provided with access to improved sanitation services
People provided with access to improved sanitation services - Female (RMS requirement)
Number of domiciliary connections to wastewater collection services increased by 2018 in the municipalities of the Sergipe river basin targeted by the project
DESO’s EBTIDA margin improved by in 2018
Establishment of classification of water bodies in the Sergipe River Basin
Elaboration of water user registry in the Sergipe River basin
Establishment and implementation of water tariffs for farmers operating within the Poção da Ribeira and Jacarecica I irrigation perimeters.
Integrated procedures and tools for environmental licensing and water rights implemented
Proposal to create or designate the state agency responsible for water resources management is submitted to the Government
Pollution load discharged by the municipalities targeted by the Project’s wastewater investments is reduced (tons of BOD/year) by 2019
Number of water utilities that the project is supporting
Reduction of energy costs in the irrigation perimeters supported by the project
